OL,3,CPrice of allotment branded 'excessive'
OL,4,Cas council plans to double rent
OL,6,FAllotment rent prices in Bristol are
OL,7,Fset to more than double by 2026.
OL,9,FThe first half of the rent hike will
OL,10,Ftake place next year, and the second
OL,11,Fhalf will be introduced in 2026.
OL,13,FRent for a medium-size plot with water
OL,14,Fwill increase from #70 to #113 next
OL,15,Fyear, and then #156 in 2026.
OL,17,FThere are 4,500 allotment plots in the
OL,18,Fcity and Bristol City Council has not
OL,19,Fincreased the rent since 2018.
